RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 68. Maiden Claiming Purse 20600. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VICTORIAN RIVIERA exchanged contact with Cataffairwithmedal leaving the gate then took the nod two deep approaching the nine sixteenths pole, dug in to the challenge of LINDA'S TAJ nearing the three eighths while alternating the lead with that one, contested even terms through the far turn and dug in determinedly to inch clear later yards. The latter raced with the pace inside, challenged toward the three eighths pole while alternating for the lead, contested even terms on the far turn and dueled gamely to mid-stretch before reluctantly ceding. WICKED SAUCY settled inside on the opening turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn then dueled through the stretch for third. SWEET FACTOR saved ground well off the pace, bid leaving the five sixteenths pole and rounded the far turn about the three path, eased out leaving the turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. SUPER SWEETIE settled off the rail on the first turn, eased out into the backstretch and picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced in the three path of the far turn and flattened in the lane. CHANTILLY MOON (PER) rounded the first turn in the three and four paths, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn. HERECOMESPUDD raced well back and never factored. CATAFFAIRWITHMEDAL exchanged contact with Sweet Factor leaving the gate, was shuffled back shortly afterward and showed little response.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 65. Allowance Purse 33900. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 27 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since February 27 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $ 12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COLT ROCK rated a slim lead leaving the chute, came under pressure nearing the quarter pole and held on under steady stretch handling. CHASENJOHNATHAN chased through the backstretch, raced in range of the lead three wide on the turn, drifted into the lane but corrected course and finished well to close the gap. DE'S CASTLE engaged in close chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail then flattened the final sixteenth. BERTRAM FLIGHT gave chase inside, raced near the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. OFFICER STONE gave chase through the backstretch, raced in range four wide on the turn, was carried out leaving the turn but ran evenly in the lane. PINNACLE REEF came away awkwardly, picked up the chase through the backstretch and saved ground on the turn. TWO ROOM SCHOOL chased the leaders, rounded the turn about the three path and showed little in the lane. JUST A FLIRT was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Colt Rock
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated slim lead inside,pressured near 1/4,steadily handled lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 7F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 32700. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 116 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUCKY ONE stalked two deep, challenged nearing the five sixteenths pole and took the nod two deep approaching the quarter, contested the edge through the far turn and dug in determinedly to inch away from ZIGGY STARDUST late yards. The latter took the lead at the thirteen sixteenths pole and rated the pace, came under pressure approaching the five sixteenths pole, was met at the rail nearing the quarter, contested near even terms through the turn and dueled gamely to deep stretch before grudgingly yielding. REVEREND JACK rated close toward the inside, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and finished well while gaining on the top two. LIEUTENANT BROWN settled off the rail on the first turn, eased out leaving the turn and gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn four wide then flattened in the lane. COMEONTURNMELOOSE settled off the rail on the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced near the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. CALLISTO'S BRIGADE rounded the opening turn in the two and three paths, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and ran evenly in the lane. I SEE NOTHING was not a factor. SENZA STRIKE stalked the early pace from the three path then faded through the backstretch. The Stewards reviewed then dismissed a claim of foul against the rider of Lucky One for alleged interference on the far turn, lodged by the rider of Ziggy Stardust.

ENTRY.NAME: Lieutenant Brown
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,eased out 1/2,chased 7/16,4wd far turn,flattened lane

ENTRY.NAME: Reverend Jack
ENTRY.OWNER: Hasty Rebel Stables LLC and Carlisle Horse Company

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ODIE took a quick lead and moved to the inside to rate the pace, came under pressure leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and dug in under steady encouragement to hold on. BAAGY rounded the opening turn in the two and three paths, bid nearing the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn, eased out entering the stretch and finished well. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROCKET APPEAL broke in and made sharp contact with Khaki Jack, dueled to a slim lead nearing the five sixteenths pole and contested the edge nearest the rail on the turn, drew clear into the lane and held on well with steady handling. REMYS SHOWTIME chased through the backstretch, contested at a close disadvantage three wide on the turn, dueled through the stretch and just lasted for second.
